The White House ’ s Advertising costs the taxpayer Thousands
The decision by the White House to fly a naval helicopter to South Lawn for an event that highlighted American manufacturing last month costs taxpayers up to $24,000, according to the military that was handed over to TIME magazine.
The green-white Sikorsky VH-3D, known as Marine One, when the president is on board, was the heart of the event at the White House on July 17 with American construction programs.
