The White House Military Office demanded the helicopter ’ s presence in a fragmentary order or FRAGO, barely 36 hours before the helicopter landed on South Lawn, according to the records of the Marine Helicopter Squadron One (HMX-1), the unit responsible for the helicopter ’ s operation.
"I just wanted you to be aware of this, because it is such an unusual event with high visibility," the commander of HMX-1 wrote on the eve of the event to his superiors, the deputy naval commander for aviation.
The news showed that the helicopter arrived on South Lawn at around 7 a.m. on July 17, for the event at 3 p.m., and stayed until the grass was cleared between 18: 00 and 21: 00 this evening.
The note adds that if departure from the White House is delayed, a second team would be required for the return flight due to the flight flight flight hours limit.
The original flight crew was at the helicopter during the event, while the unit ’ s security staff remained on the ground during the period.
It was not clear from the TIME records that a second flight crew was ultimately required.
The Hatch Act prohibits federal employees from using state property for political purposes.
Data sets indicate that HMX-1 asked if the event could break the determination.
"One question we asked was whether it was a violation of the Hatch Act and we were informed that this was not the case," the commander wrote.
"Sounds as if you are closed," the deputy commander replied.
The 'Made in America' event was described by the White House as an official event and would not have been covered by the Hatch Act.
But official events also have political overtones.
At the event, the President launched the reform of the health reform under way in the Senate, and he propagated the efforts to contain government regulations.
The use of the aircraft known as Marine One or Air Force One for politically advantageous purposes is hardly a new phenomenon.
Presidents are obliged to use them for the journey.
But to request their use only for a photo-surgery is unusual.
Trump conducted an investigation in February, when the presidential plane provided taxi services against the backdrop of its first campaign rally in Melbourne, Florida, and his Twitter account is full of news complaining about his predecessor ’ s use of the presidential plane.
"The White House is enthusiastic about the show" Made in America "- which shows products from all 50 countries produced by American workers using American materials," said the Deputy Press Secretary of the White House, Lindsay Walters.
HMX-1 crews often fly training flights in the Washington area and South Lawn to remove the US president at the White House with precise centimeters.
